WEBVTT

00:03.337 --> 00:06.005
Do you know what this is? What?

00:06.007 --> 00:08.707
This is a picture
of our entire class swimming

00:08.709 --> 00:10.809
at Dominique Harris'
birthday bash.

00:10.811 --> 00:12.778
Do you see<i> us?</i>
Do you?

00:12.780 --> 00:13.946
Look hard!

00:13.948 --> 00:15.114
Take it down a notch, friend.

00:15.116 --> 00:17.816
You don't see us
because we're not in it.

00:17.818 --> 00:19.651
Because we weren't invited.

00:19.653 --> 00:20.686
Because of you people!

00:20.688 --> 00:21.720
What did we do?

00:21.722 --> 00:23.856
Probably said no,
like you usually do.

00:23.858 --> 00:25.791
That's why I just lie to you
about where I'm going.

00:25.793 --> 00:26.792
What...

00:26.794 --> 00:28.360
Dre: Zoey,
where are you going?

00:28.362 --> 00:30.579
To bed.

00:30.580 --> 00:32.797
Dre: <i>Zoey, while a boldfaced
liar, wasn't wrong.</i>

00:32.800 --> 00:35.034
<i>Bow and I are "no" people.</i>

00:35.036 --> 00:36.869
<i>When people ask us
to do stuff...</i>

00:36.871 --> 00:38.837
So, we're having a party
for Sophie this Saturday.

00:38.839 --> 00:39.805
Can you make it?

00:39.807 --> 00:41.740
<i>Our default position is</i>

00:41.741 --> 00:43.674
<i>"home is where our heart
and our butts are."</i>

00:43.677 --> 00:44.843
We'd love to!

00:44.845 --> 00:46.578
Unless it's Saturday.

00:46.580 --> 00:49.515
Ooh, can't.
My aunt Edith died.

00:49.517 --> 00:50.749
Can't.
Broke my leg.

00:50.751 --> 00:52.918
Walking around on
a broken femur right now.

00:52.920 --> 00:55.921
I am strong, but not smart.

00:55.923 --> 00:58.891
No. Uh...
Another dead aunt.

00:58.893 --> 01:01.693
My aunt e... condoleezza.

01:01.695 --> 01:04.496
Your excuse game is in shambles.

01:04.498 --> 01:05.764
Aunt Condoleezza?

01:05.766 --> 01:08.834
You're absolutely right,
walking broken femur.

01:08.836 --> 01:11.570
Can you two please
just start saying "yes" more?

01:11.572 --> 01:13.272
Please?

01:13.774 --> 01:16.842
So, the party is Saturday?
David: Yeah.

01:16.844 --> 01:18.577
You can make it, right?

01:19.847 --> 01:23.482
They have a pool.
With a slide.

01:26.454 --> 01:27.519
Both: Yes.

01:32.793 --> 01:35.594
Dre: Man, I should go over there
and jump up in there.

01:35.596 --> 01:36.728
Rainbow: No.

01:36.730 --> 01:38.030
Yeah, make one of the kids
just fly over the top.

01:38.032 --> 01:39.198
Diane: Hey!
We're going to the pool!

01:39.200 --> 01:40.699
Jack: The pool! Rainbow:
Going to the pool!

01:40.701 --> 01:41.934
Hey, buddy system. Yeah.

01:41.936 --> 01:43.635
Buddy system! Go!
Have fun, you guys.

01:43.637 --> 01:45.604
All right, hey, I got to say,

01:45.606 --> 01:46.805
the coopers have found out

01:46.807 --> 01:49.441
the secret to having
a good kids' party.

01:49.443 --> 01:50.576
Liquor.
Boom!

01:50.578 --> 01:53.378
Dre, why didn't we think
of booze?

01:53.380 --> 01:54.930
We got to do better.

01:54.931 --> 01:56.481
I can't lie.
I'm having a great time.

01:56.484 --> 01:58.634
Mm-hmm.

01:58.635 --> 02:00.785
And it wouldn't hurt us to
say "yes" more often. Yeah.

02:00.788 --> 02:01.787
Okay?
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

02:01.789 --> 02:03.455
Want another Margarita?

02:04.825 --> 02:05.891
Yes!
See?

02:05.893 --> 02:07.126
It's already paying off.

02:07.128 --> 02:08.927
You guys, thank you so much
for having us.

02:08.929 --> 02:10.562
We're so happy
you all could make it.

02:10.564 --> 02:11.797
We're having a great time.

02:11.799 --> 02:12.764
Uh-oh.

02:12.766 --> 02:13.799
Jack is waist-deep
in the pool,

02:13.801 --> 02:15.317
and he's got that look
in his eyes.

02:15.318 --> 02:16.834
Okay. Okay. Go handle it. Go handle it.
So I'm gonna...

02:16.837 --> 02:17.903
Margaritas!

02:17.905 --> 02:19.905
Margaritas!
[ Laughs ]

02:19.907 --> 02:22.641
You know, we should
get together again.

02:22.643 --> 02:23.675
Yeah.

02:23.677 --> 02:25.744
Okay, let's make it happen.

02:25.746 --> 02:27.012
Okay.

02:27.014 --> 02:28.914
I know we haven't
known each other that long,

02:28.916 --> 02:31.350
but why don't you all come
with us to church next Sunday?

02:31.352 --> 02:33.569
Church?

02:33.570 --> 02:35.787
<i>The reason I'm pausing here
is because for black folks,</i>

02:35.789 --> 02:37.940
<i>church is a big deal.</i>

02:37.941 --> 02:40.092
<i>For centuries, it's been
the backbone of our community,</i>

02:40.094 --> 02:43.028
<i>dating back
to when we first got here.</i>

02:43.030 --> 02:45.964
<i>Some even say
the term "Sunday best"</i>

02:45.966 --> 02:48.800
<i>came from slaves
having one good outfit</i>

02:48.802 --> 02:50.802
<i>their owners bought them
for church,</i>

02:50.804 --> 02:54.473
<i>which to be fair,
we kind of ran with...</i>

02:54.475 --> 02:55.641
<i>And ran...</i>

02:55.643 --> 02:57.376
<i>And ran...</i>

02:57.378 --> 02:59.762
<i>And ran.</i>

02:59.763 --> 03:02.147
<i>Churches were not only the core
of the civil rights movement,</i>

03:02.149 --> 03:06.852
<i>but also the one place you knew
your mama couldn't beat you.</i>

03:07.288 --> 03:10.856
<i>Growing up,
it's how we spent our Sundays.</i>

03:10.858 --> 03:12.775
<i>Don't get me wrong...</i>

03:12.776 --> 03:14.693
<i>I still have my faith,
but in the Johnson home,</i>

03:14.695 --> 03:16.828
<i>this is what Sundays
have become.</i>

03:16.830 --> 03:18.897
All right, Zoey...
Sat prep.

03:18.899 --> 03:20.566
Junior...
Field hockey.

03:20.568 --> 03:21.833
Jack...
Basketball.

03:21.835 --> 03:23.669
Diane...
Court-mandated therapy.

03:23.671 --> 03:24.803
Let's go!

03:24.805 --> 03:26.738
♪ It ain't nothin'
but a party goin' on ♪

03:26.740 --> 03:28.807
I did not make it to Jack
in time,

03:28.809 --> 03:29.908
but if we get out of here
right now,

03:29.910 --> 03:31.543
it'll get pinned
on Nicky Schultz.

03:31.545 --> 03:32.578
Let's go.
Okay, hold...

03:32.580 --> 03:34.012
Come on, let's...
Uh, in other news,

03:34.014 --> 03:38.150
I may have committed us
to church on Sunday.

03:38.152 --> 03:38.717
Church?

03:38.719 --> 03:39.685
Yes.

03:39.687 --> 03:41.653
No!

03:41.655 --> 03:43.689
What?
What were you thinking?

03:43.691 --> 03:45.724
I felt guilty.
It was church.

03:45.726 --> 03:47.059
And let's face it, bow...

03:47.061 --> 03:49.161
We're c.E.O. Churchgoers
at best.

03:49.163 --> 03:49.995
What does that mean?

03:49.997 --> 03:51.830
"Christmas and Easter
only."

03:51.832 --> 03:53.031
No, we're not.

03:53.033 --> 03:55.100
The last time we went
was on... Easter.

03:55.102 --> 03:57.569
Well, okay, the time
before that... Christmas.

03:57.571 --> 03:58.937
Look, I know
it doesn't matter to you

03:58.939 --> 04:01.373
since you were raised
by a godless hippie...

04:01.375 --> 04:02.608
Correction.

04:02.610 --> 04:04.676
She believed in many goddesses

04:04.678 --> 04:06.612
and the healing power
of tree nuts.

04:06.614 --> 04:08.580
But I'm with you, Dre, okay?

04:08.582 --> 04:09.748
A little more church
wouldn't kill us,

04:09.750 --> 04:10.882
and it'd be good for the kids.

04:10.884 --> 04:12.618
Especially Diane.

04:12.620 --> 04:14.386
Therapy is not working.

04:14.388 --> 04:15.687
At all.

04:15.689 --> 04:16.888
Okay, guys, listen up.

04:16.890 --> 04:20.459
On Sunday,
we are going to church.

04:20.461 --> 04:21.960
Why?!
No!

04:21.962 --> 04:23.862
We just went six months ago.

04:23.864 --> 04:25.797
You guys,
the coopers invited us,

04:25.799 --> 04:27.633
and you wanted us
to say "yes" more.

04:27.635 --> 04:28.767
I could do church.

04:28.769 --> 04:30.969
I'd love to get one more wear
out of my Easter suit

04:30.971 --> 04:33.705
before it gets too small.

04:33.707 --> 04:35.707
Growing like a weed.
Okay.

04:35.709 --> 04:36.908
Ruby: Andre?
Hmm?

04:36.910 --> 04:39.444
I've been asking you to go
to church with me for years.

04:39.446 --> 04:40.612
God knows my heart.

04:40.613 --> 04:41.779
Yeah, but he don't
know your face.

04:41.782 --> 04:44.716
And now white folks call,
and here you come.

04:44.718 --> 04:45.784
Oh, Ruby, it's not like that.

04:45.786 --> 04:46.818
Mnh-mnh.

04:46.820 --> 04:48.754
Oh, really?
Mm-hmm.

04:48.756 --> 04:49.955
Are you the expert,

04:49.957 --> 04:52.791
late-in-life Christian,
ex-snake charmer?

04:52.793 --> 04:54.559
It was just once.

04:54.561 --> 04:55.894
I just thank the lord on high

04:55.896 --> 04:58.730
I was able to get you
to baptize these babies.

04:58.732 --> 05:00.799
Mm...

05:00.801 --> 05:02.734
Everybody, let's go get
cleaned up for dinner.

05:02.736 --> 05:03.902
Dinnertime!
Dinnertime!

05:03.904 --> 05:06.571
Wait, when did the twins
get baptized?

05:06.573 --> 05:07.739
I don't remember going.

05:07.741 --> 05:08.807
Me neither.

05:08.809 --> 05:11.643
Uh...
Mama, you missed it

05:11.645 --> 05:13.679
when you followed A.C. Green
to Montego bay

05:13.681 --> 05:14.946
and tried to take his virginity.

05:14.948 --> 05:17.683
Try?
[ Laughs ]

05:17.685 --> 05:20.252
"How Ruby got
her groove back."

05:21.622 --> 05:23.922
I wore the hell
out of those braids.

05:23.924 --> 05:26.792
Yeah. She wore 'em for like
a year too long. Mm-hmm.

05:26.794 --> 05:30.362
Wait a minute.
That trip was 15 years ago.

05:32.599 --> 05:34.633
Oh, don't tell me.

05:34.635 --> 05:37.469
Look, mama, don't be mad.

05:37.471 --> 05:38.770
But...
Sweet Jesus.

05:38.772 --> 05:41.006
It may be a possibility...
Mnh-mnh!

05:41.008 --> 05:43.442
That we never...
Oh, no!

05:43.444 --> 05:45.611
Baptized the twins.

05:45.612 --> 05:47.779
Ohhhh, sweet heavenly Jesus,
keep me near the cross!

05:47.781 --> 05:49.948
Ruby! I think you're being
a little dramatic.

05:49.950 --> 05:52.851
I have never been dramatic a day
in my life. Okay. All right.

05:52.853 --> 05:54.886
Not ever, ever, ever.
Okay, Dre...

05:54.888 --> 05:57.356
Ever, ever, ever, ever, ever!

05:58.525 --> 05:59.558
Come to grandma.

05:59.560 --> 06:00.859
Now, listen.

06:00.861 --> 06:02.828
I want you two
to be very careful,

06:02.830 --> 06:05.697
because it doesn't matter
how good you are...

06:05.699 --> 06:08.667
When you die,
you're going to a place

06:08.669 --> 06:11.636
that is hotter and darker
than the bowels of hell.

06:11.638 --> 06:12.738
What?!

06:12.740 --> 06:13.839
Mommy?

06:13.841 --> 06:14.973
Ruby!
That's enough.

06:14.975 --> 06:18.677
I am going to get helmets
for these babies' heads.

06:18.679 --> 06:21.213
[ Sighs shakily ]

06:22.983 --> 06:25.751
I don't want to go to
a place worse than hell.

06:25.753 --> 06:28.086
I've already been
to a wnba game!

06:28.088 --> 06:30.922
Wake up, amigo.
I've been thinking about it.

06:30.924 --> 06:33.658
This is our free pass
to do whatever we want.

06:33.660 --> 06:34.726
What do you mean?

06:34.728 --> 06:37.562
If we're damned if we do
and damned if we don't,

06:37.564 --> 06:39.698
I say we do.
I say we don't.

06:39.700 --> 06:41.500
Put your helmet on.

06:41.502 --> 06:42.701
Why are you tempting fate?

06:42.703 --> 06:44.669
We live in earthquake country.

06:45.906 --> 06:49.040
<i>So, Sunday, we found ourselves
at the coopers' church.</i>

06:49.042 --> 06:54.413
♪ How sweet it is
to be loved by you ♪

06:55.682 --> 06:57.883
♪ Oh, whoa, whoa ♪

06:57.885 --> 07:02.621
♪ How sweet it is
to be loved by you ♪

07:04.725 --> 07:05.757
Babe.
What?

07:05.759 --> 07:06.958
This isn't bad at all. Mnh-mnh.

07:06.960 --> 07:08.894
I love how the minister
wasn't preachy.

07:08.896 --> 07:10.095
He used, like, metaphors. Right?

07:10.097 --> 07:13.031
Life<i> is</i> like a house
with a lot of rooms.

07:13.033 --> 07:15.734
And I am feeling this band.

07:15.736 --> 07:17.736
And that bass player
is in the pocket.

07:17.738 --> 07:20.772
Ah, junior's in the pocket, too, babe.
Look. Hmm?

07:20.774 --> 07:22.707
♪ I just want to stop ♪

07:22.709 --> 07:23.875
[ Instruments stop ]

07:23.877 --> 07:25.477
[ Instruments resume ]
♪ and thank you, baby ♪

07:25.479 --> 07:27.646
Ooh!
♪ Oh, yeah ♪

07:27.648 --> 07:30.782
That whole thing
about exiting the dark hall

07:30.784 --> 07:32.884
and finding the bright path...

07:32.886 --> 07:34.052
Where'd you get that from?

07:34.054 --> 07:37.389
Uh, I was telling people
where the bathrooms are.

07:37.391 --> 07:39.508
Amazing.

07:39.509 --> 07:41.626
Do Presbyterians not believe
in cell service?

07:43.764 --> 07:45.564
[ Laughs ]

07:45.566 --> 07:46.765
What are you doing?

07:46.767 --> 07:50.469
God is not watching us.
Yes, he is!

07:50.471 --> 07:51.736
God's everywhere.

07:51.738 --> 07:54.506
Ugh.
Except wnba games.

07:54.508 --> 07:56.308
Nobody goes to those.

07:58.479 --> 07:59.862
Is it crazy

07:59.863 --> 08:01.246
that this is one of the best
Sundays I've had in a while?

08:01.248 --> 08:04.783
I mean, ever since Jack made me
give up those wnba tickets.

08:04.785 --> 08:07.586
I know, right? Hey, bow... Huh?

08:07.588 --> 08:09.488
This could be our spot.

08:09.490 --> 08:11.089
Tight 45-minute service,

08:11.091 --> 08:13.859
the rev got us out in time to
beat the Methodists to brunch?

08:13.861 --> 08:15.927
[ Laughs ] Dre, we seriously
need to say "yes" more.

08:15.929 --> 08:17.762
Can you imagine how different
our lives would be

08:17.764 --> 08:19.431
if we didn't say "no" so much?

08:19.967 --> 08:21.867
Ohh! Wait.
What, what?

08:21.869 --> 08:24.002
We both know we don't want children.
Mnh-mnh.

08:24.004 --> 08:26.705
Should we use protection?

08:26.707 --> 08:28.373
Both: Nah!

08:29.142 --> 08:31.643
Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait.
What, what?

08:31.645 --> 08:32.677
Baby...
What?

08:32.679 --> 08:33.945
We already have two kids. Okay.

08:33.947 --> 08:35.814
Should we use protection?

08:35.816 --> 08:36.882
Both: Nah!

08:36.884 --> 08:39.017
With two kids,
I could've kept that pt cruiser.

08:39.019 --> 08:40.819
That's a good argument
for four kids.

08:40.821 --> 08:42.387
Oh, oh, look who's coming.

08:42.389 --> 08:43.622
Hey!
Hi!

08:43.624 --> 08:45.023
What'd you think?

08:45.025 --> 08:47.859
You guys, thank you so much
for inviting us.

08:47.861 --> 08:49.027
Thank you for coming.

08:49.029 --> 08:51.129
Oh, god, we're so glad we
came to check it out. Yes.

08:51.131 --> 08:52.998
You should really come back
and join us next week.

08:53.000 --> 08:53.798
[ Both gasp ]

08:53.800 --> 08:55.367
Yeah, will you join us?

08:55.369 --> 08:58.370
[ Both stammer ]

08:58.372 --> 08:59.538
Both: Yes!

09:02.643 --> 09:04.309
Hey.

09:04.311 --> 09:05.594
Oh!

09:05.595 --> 09:06.878
Brothers and sisters,
good morning!

09:06.880 --> 09:08.079
Boop! [ Chuckles ]

09:08.081 --> 09:11.650
Whoa. Dre, you seem
unusually chipper for a Monday.

09:11.652 --> 09:12.651
What's wrong?

09:12.653 --> 09:13.985
Got my "yes" game on yesterday,

09:13.987 --> 09:16.087
and I took my family to church.

09:16.089 --> 09:19.891
Wasn't looking forward to it,
but I felt great after.

09:19.893 --> 09:22.327
Like a massage from a man.

09:22.329 --> 09:23.361
Hmm?

09:23.363 --> 09:24.496
Strong hands.

09:24.498 --> 09:26.048
Yeah.

09:26.049 --> 09:27.599
You know, I'm thinking about
going back next week.

09:27.601 --> 09:28.767
Going back?
Uh-huh.

09:28.769 --> 09:30.936
Okay, you're not getting
all churchy on me, are you?

09:30.938 --> 09:33.038
You know,
looking for those free holidays,

09:33.040 --> 09:36.608
like this one over here
with her, uh, "second new year"?

09:36.610 --> 09:38.076
Okay, one... I don't see
anyone complaining

09:38.078 --> 09:40.712
when I'm on the phone with Tokyo
on Christmas morning,

09:40.714 --> 09:42.113
and two...
I'm proud to be a Jew.

09:42.115 --> 09:43.682
Oh, whoa, whoa, whoa.
Come on. What?

09:43.684 --> 09:45.517
Stop being self-hating.

09:45.519 --> 09:47.719
Respect yourself, girl.
Yes!

09:47.721 --> 09:49.054
It's okay.
We call ourselves Jews.

09:49.056 --> 09:52.290
Not in this office you don't,
little lady.

09:52.292 --> 09:54.042
I do church.

09:54.043 --> 09:55.793
I even co-signed
for my reverend's Bentley.

09:55.796 --> 09:59.564
My son can't buy a hot lunch,
but, uh, I'm going to heaven.

09:59.566 --> 10:00.699
Do you go every Sunday?

10:00.701 --> 10:01.733
Well, pretty much,

10:01.735 --> 10:03.702
unless I'm getting a massage
from David.

10:03.704 --> 10:04.636
Ooh.

10:04.638 --> 10:06.137
Look, just be careful, okay?

10:06.139 --> 10:09.074
You go to church three times,
you get locked in,

10:09.076 --> 10:12.811
the same way that... You sleep
with a woman for the third time,

10:12.813 --> 10:14.112
well, then she becomes
your mistress.

10:14.114 --> 10:16.948
Next thing you know,
you've bought her an apartment

10:16.950 --> 10:19.718
on the Wilshire corridor
right next to pia zadora

10:19.720 --> 10:20.785
and a Jersey Mike's.

10:20.787 --> 10:23.455
That's why when I buy
a three-pack of rubbers,

10:23.457 --> 10:24.789
I throw the third one out.

10:24.791 --> 10:26.591
Reminds me to pull out.

10:26.593 --> 10:27.792
Ugh!
Ew.

10:27.794 --> 10:28.793
Of the relationship.

10:28.795 --> 10:31.630
No, no.
Don't listen to them, Dre, okay?

10:31.632 --> 10:33.732
I think weekly worship
is a good thing.

10:33.734 --> 10:34.899
As a practicing Jew, I...

10:34.901 --> 10:36.801
- Okay!
- Oh!

10:36.803 --> 10:39.804
You take your hateful mouth
to h.R. Right now.

10:39.806 --> 10:41.239
I...
Go.

10:41.241 --> 10:44.242
<i>So my boss didn't get exactly
where I was coming from...</i>

10:44.244 --> 10:47.145
<i>Or anywhere near
where I was coming from.</i>

10:47.147 --> 10:50.915
Babe. Stevens acted like
I'm getting all churchy.

10:50.917 --> 10:53.418
Are we getting all churchy?

10:53.419 --> 10:55.920
No. We're just making a little
more time for it for a change.

10:55.922 --> 10:57.822
You know, that was something
that I never did,

10:57.824 --> 10:58.990
because growing up as a kid,

10:58.992 --> 11:00.759
church was shoved down
my throat,

11:00.761 --> 11:01.860
and I didn't like it.

11:01.862 --> 11:03.928
Well, at least only one
was forced on you.

11:03.930 --> 11:05.830
I had, like, 30.
Hmm.

11:05.832 --> 11:09.000
And after the naked church,
I was totally turned off.

